headline: Does Home Depot’s Modest 2026 Outlook And Dividend Hike Reframe The Tech‑And‑Pro Story For HD?
summary: Earlier this week, Home Depot reported fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results showing quarterly sales of US$38.20 billion and net income of US$2.57 billion, alongside guidance for 2026 that calls for total sales growth of about 2.5% to 4.5% and flat to 4% diluted EPS growth. The company also approved a 1.3% dividend increase to US$2.33 per share, plans to open about 15 new stores in 2026, and continues to lean on its professional customer ecosystem to support performance despite a...
